comment._content: Talking of cars, notice the beautiful Citroen 11L in the intersection. Most probably a pre-1952 model as there was a larger boot from 1952 onward. However, according to one source, all Citroens were black until 1953, yet this vehicle does not seem to be black! Being a RH drive model, it would have been built in Slough, UK.
